               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Collection of medical tracts of Yusufi, who was active in India under Babur and Humayun by Yūsufī, Yūsuf ibn Muḥammad, 16th cent.
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_Uncat_6-item1">
                     <author key="person_31540986" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/31540986/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Yūsufī, Yūsuf ibn Muḥammad, 16th cent.</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en" key="work_9827">Collection of medical tracts of Yusufi, who was active in India under Babur and Humayun.</title>
                     <note>Contains, with reference to Storey's list of Yusufi's works. a) Sittah-i Daruriyyah. 6ff. Storey No 15. b) Qasidah dar Hifz-i Sihhat. 3ff. (Storey No 12). c) Nuskah dar Tadbir-i Ma'kul u Mashrub. In verse. 4ff. (Storey No 7). d) Qasidah dar Bayan-i Adwiyah. 2ff, On Arabic and Persian names for medicaments. (Storey No 8 cf. No 10). f) Jami' al-Fawa'id. 54ff. (Storey No 6). These items with the addition of the Fawa'id al-Akhyar (Storey No 4) and the Dala'il al-Nabd wa Dala'l al-Baul (Storey Nos 2 and 3) are listed with correct folio counts on the verso of the first page of b). Headings and punctuation etc in red, occasionally blue. Ruled margins.</note>
                     <incipit>Incipit of item a): Al-hamdu lillahi al-mun'im li-hayat al-nufus</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, ii, pp. 235-9.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
